6. Dost thou hate and abhorr, loath and detest all Sin; 
                     Sign. 6 Heart sins, and Conversation sins, open sins, and secret evils? Dost thou hate vain Thoughts,Psa: 119.104, 113, 163. and all the motions and workings of sin and corruptions in thy Members? And art thou truly burdened with the filth of Sin, as well as thou hast been with the guilt of Sin?Ezek. 36.31. And dost thou loath thy self for thy Sins, groan under them, cry out against them, desiring to be rid of them, saying unto the Lord,Hos. 14.2.
                  Take away all Iniquity, and receive me graciously: so will I render thee the calves (the praise of my Heart, and) of my Lips? Then, O then, be of good comfort, fear not, for God has been gracious to thy Soul, Hos. 14.2.
